<div class="recipe-container">
    <h1>Channa Masala Recipe</h1>

    <div class="recipe-description">
        <p><strong>Channa Masala</strong> is a flavorful North Indian dish made with chickpeas cooked in a spicy and tangy tomato-based gravy. It’s a popular vegetarian dish that is both healthy and delicious, making it a favorite in Indian households and restaurants alike.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <div class="ingredient-list">
            <div class="ingredient-item">For the Gravy:
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups cooked Chickpeas (or 1 can of chickpeas)</li>
                    <li>1 large Onion, finely chopped</li>
                    <li>2 Tomatoes, pureed</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Ginger-garlic paste</li>
                    <li>1-2 Green chilies, slit</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Cumin seeds</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Red chili powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Coriander powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Garam masala</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Lemon juice</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                    <li>Fresh cilantro leaves for garnish</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cooking-instructions">
        <h2>How to Cook</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Prepare the Chickpeas:</strong> If using dried chickpeas, soak them overnight and cook them in a pressure cooker. If using canned chickpeas, drain and rinse them thoroughly.</li>
            <li><strong>Prepare the Gravy:</strong> Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds, and allow them to splutter. Add the chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for 1 minute. Then, add the pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil begins to separate from the masala (spices).</li>
            <li>Now add turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, and salt. Stir well and cook for 2-3 minutes.</li>
            <li>Pour in the cooked chickpeas and add 1-2 cups of water to make the gravy. Simmer for 15-20 minutes so the chickpeas absorb the flavors.</li>
            <li>Finish off by adding garam masala and lemon juice. Stir well and cook for another 2 minutes.</li>
            <li><strong>Garnish & Serve:</strong> Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves before serving.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tips">
        <h2>Tips & Variations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>You can add a pinch of Asafoetida (Hing) for extra flavor.</li>
            <li>If you prefer a smoother gravy, you can blend the cooked onions and tomatoes before adding the chickpeas.</li>
            <li>To make it spicy, add more green chilies or a pinch of red chili flakes.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="serve">
        <h2>Serving Suggestions</h2>
        <p>Channa Masala is best enjoyed with soft, warm naan, roti, or steamed rice. You can also serve it with a side of yogurt or a simple cucumber salad to balance the spice.</p>
    </div>
</div>
